0American%20dream.%20In%20the%20internet's%20collective%20imagination%2C%20Steven%20Mnuchin%20%3Cem%3Ewould%20never%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street's%20approach%20to%20Trump%20has%20long%20had%20an%20element%20of%20wishful%20thinking%20to%20it.%20Yes%2C%20the%20president%20likes%20to%20tell%20people%20their%20stocks%20are%20going%20to%20go%20up%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20the%20Republican%20Party's%20bent%20toward%20low%20taxes%20and%20deregulation%20is%20something%20the%20business%20community%20favors.%20But%20the%20thing%20about%20Trump%20is%20that%20he%20says%20and%20believes%20a%20lot%20of%20things%2C%20and%20not%20all%20of%20his%20ideas%20are%20music%20to%20investors'%20ears%2C%20especially%20lately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration's%20order%20of%20operations%20this%20time%20around%20may%20not%20be%20so%20favorable%20to%20the%20stock%20market%20or%20economy%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20He's%20focused%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-winners-losers-trump-tariffs-stagflation-manufacturing-mexico-canada-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20been%20announcing%2C%20delaying%2C%20and%20reinstating%20them%20at%20a%20breakneck%20pace.%20When%20he%20was%20elected%2C%20many%20observers%20believed%20tariffs%20were%20largely%20going%20to%20be%20a%20negotiation%20tactic.%20Six%20weeks%20into%20his%20presidency%2C%20it's%20becoming%20clear%20he%20means%20business%2C%20even%20if%20the%20exact%20details%20of%20said%20business%20remain%20TBD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20a%20different%20environment%20in%20Trump%202%20than%20Trump%201%2C%20and%20I%20think%20one%20of%20the%20differences%20is%20that%20there's%20more%20broad%20agreement%20on%20the%20use%20of%20protectionist%20policies%2C%20even%20by%20the%20so-called%20Wall%20Street%20voices%2C%26quot%3B%20Josh%20Lipsky%2C%20the%20senior%20director%20of%20the%20Atlantic%20Council's%20GeoEconomics%20Center%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20first%20administration%2C%20they%20didn't%20even%20start%20talking%20about%20tariffs%20seriously%20until%20a%20year%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20markets%20have%20started%20to%20flash%20warning%20signs%20about%20the%20tariff%20whiplash%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20response%20has%20been%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20shrug.%20In%20his%20address%20to%20a%20joint%20session%20of%20Congress%20last%20week%2C%20the%20president%20acknowledged%20tariffs%20would%20cause%20a%20%26quot%3Blittle%20disturbance%26quot%3B%20but%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20OK%20with%20that.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20subsequent%20interview%20with%20Fox%20News%2C%20he%20wouldn't%20close%20the%20door%20on%20a%20possible%20recession%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20hate%20to%20predict%20things%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%20Bessent%20recently%20told%20CNBC%20that%20maybe%20the%20economy%20is%20%26quot%3Bstarting%20to%20roll%20a%20little%20bit%26quot%3B%20and%20predicted%20a%20%26quot%3Bdetox%20period%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20government%20slows%20its%20spending.%20After%20Trump's%20recession%20hedge%2C%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%20said%20there%20won't%20be%20a%20recession%20in%20America%20%E2%80%94%20but%20Lutnick's%20also%20been%20tasked%20with%20trying%20to%20explain%20the%20daily%20flip-flops%20on%20tariffs%2C%20which%20seems%20to%20have%20undercut%20Wall%20Street's%20faith%20in%20his%20pronouncements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20tariffs%2C%20Trump%20is%20looking%20to%20move%20fast%20on%20immigration%20and%20deportations%2C%20another%20check%20in%20the%20negative%20column%20for%20many%20businesses.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmanagement-experts-musk-doge-case-study-bad-management-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echaos%20DOGE%20is%20creating%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Oh%2C%20and%20did%20I%20mention%20there's%20perhaps%20a%20government%20shutdown%20on%20the%20horizon%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20happening%20now%20is%20you've%20got%20animal%20spirits%20meeting%20up%20with%20the%20realities%20of%20policy%20on%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20Gregory%20Faranello%2C%20the%20head%20of%20US%20rates%20trading%20and%20strategy%20for%20AmeriVet%20Securities%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20total%20pool%20and%20bucket%20of%20everything%20that's%20going%20on%20right%20now%2C%20it's%20uncertainty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20uncertainty%20probably%20won't%20last%20forever%2C%20but%20right%20now%2C%20it's%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20on%20edge.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20is%20down%20by%205%25%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%2C%20and%20the%20Dow%20by%203%25.%20Many%20smart%20people%20did%20not%20expect%20to%20be%20in%20%26quot%3Bdon't-look-at-your-401(k)%26quot%3B%20territory%20this%20early%20in%20Trump's%20second%20term%2C%20if%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FxwmMQ%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Stocks%20in%20Trump's%20first%20hundred%20days%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22511%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCapricious%20policies%20are%20likely%20to%20freeze%20any%20kind%20of%20capital%20investment%20or%20business%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jack%20Ablin%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20officer%20and%20founding%20partner%20of%20Cresset%20Capital.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20problematic%20in%20an%20economy%20that%20appears%20to%20be%20slowing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20necessarily%20the%20case%20that%20Trump%202.0%20doesn't%20care%20at%20all%20about%20Wall%20Street%3B%20he%20just%20seems%20to%20care%20about%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20things%20more.%20The%20White%20House%20contends%20that%20while%20tariffs%2C%20for%20example%2C%20might%20be%20a%20pain%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%20they're%20necessary%20to%20revamp%20the%20economy%20over%20the%20long%20haul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%202.0%20is%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20more%20holistic%20on%20what%20they're%20looking%20at%20to%20define%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20Keith%20Lerner%2C%20chief%20market%20strategist%20at%20Truist%20Wealth%2C%20said.%20Bessent%20seems%20quite%20focused%20on%20the%20bond%20market%20and%2010-year%20Treasurys%2C%20specifically%2C%20believing%20lower%20bond%20yields%20might%20help%20boost%20the%20housing%20market.%20He%20has%20characterized%20tariffs%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bone-time%20price%20adjustment%26quot%3B%20and%20brushed%20off%20concerns%20about%20inflation%20in%20his%20defense%20of%20the%20administration's%20trade%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20the%20question%20is%2C%20OK%2C%20holistically%2C%20you%20have%20a%207%25%20decline%20in%20the%20stock%20market.%20From%20their%20perspective%2C%20that%20may%20be%20OK%20relative%20to%20these%20other%20things%20which%20are%20priorities%20for%20them%20and%20will%20make%20the%20US%20economy%20more%20competitive%2C%26quot%3B%20Lerner%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20question%20that%20no%20one%20knows%20is%20what's%20the%20pain%20threshold%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20assumption%20has%20long%20been%20that%20the%20markets%20would%20check%20Trump's%20worst%20impulses%20(or%20a%20Mnuchin-like%20figure%20who%20would%20hammer%20home%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20the%20markets).%20Right%20now%2C%20the%20checkpoint%20isn't%20clear.%20Bessent%20seems%20to%20be%20aligned%20with%20the%20president's%20protectionist%20stance%2C%20and%20Wall%20Street%20doesn't%20find%20him%20to%20be%20a%20particularly%20soothing%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Street%20is%20not%20comfortable%20yet%20with%20Bessent%20and%20Lutnick%2C%20and%20that's%20been%20an%20overhang%20and%20issue%20for%20the%20markets%20in%20the%20near%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20Dan%20Ives%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20Wedbush%20Securities%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20stock%20market's%20meltdown%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20White%20House%20released%20a%20statement%20from%20an%20unnamed%20official%20arguing%20that%20Wall%20Street%20fears%20aren't%20necessarily%20reflective%20of%20what's%20happening%20in%20the%20real%20economy.%20%26quot%3BWant%20to%20emphasize%20that%20we're%20seeing%20a%20strong%20divergence%20between%20animal%20spirits%20of%20the%20stock%20market%20and%20what%20we're%20actually%20seeing%20unfold%20from%20businesses%20and%20business%20leaders%2C%20and%20the%20latter%20is%20obviously%20more%20meaningful%20than%20the%20former%20on%20what's%20in%20store%20for%20the%20economy%20in%20the%20medium%20to%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20businesses%20are%20not%20having%20a%20good%20time%20trying%20to%20decipher%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-dei-tariffs-taxes-business-uncertainty-scaredy-cat-capitalism-anxiety-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolicy%20uncertainty%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20problem%20with%20opening%20the%20door%20to%20a%20small%20recession%20or%20adjustment%20period%20is%20that%20once%20a%20downturn%20has%20begun%2C%20there's%20no%20control%20over%20what%20happens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRecessions%20are%20their%20own%20beasts%2C%26quot%3B%20Kevin%20Gordon%2C%20a%20senior%20investment%20strategist%20at%20Charles%20Schwab%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20could%20take%20on%20a%20pretty%20strong%20position%20in%20terms%20of%20changing%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20economy.%20So%20it's%20certainly%20something%20I'd%20say%20be%20careful%20what%20you%20wish%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20upheaval%2C%20Wall%20Street%20still%20has%20things%20to%20be%20excited%20about%20in%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20sugar%20high%20is%20wearing%20off%20a%20bit%2C%20and%20some%20less%20favorable%20realities%20are%20setting%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20some%20of%20the%20thrilling%20stuff%20the%20administration%20is%20expected%20to%20deliver%20is%20not%20that%20thrilling%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20the%20tax%20bill.%20Many%20of%20the%20provisions%20in%20Trump's%202017%20tax%20bill%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-pay-in-taxes-trump-tax-bill-expiring-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eset%20to%20expire%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Trump%20and%20the%20GOP-led%20Congress%20are%20highly%20likely%20to%20pass%20a%20new%20bill%20to%20extend%20most%20of%20them.%20For%20corporations%20and%20individuals%2C%20the%20extension%20is%20good%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20their%20tax%20bills%20won't%20go%20up.%20But%20it's%20not%20as%20great%20as%20it%20was%20in%202017%20when%20they%20got%20a%20massive%20new%20cut.%20Keeping%20the%202017%20law%20is%20%26quot%3Bjust%20extending%20the%20status%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20there%20is%20no%20additional%20stimulus%20that%20comes%20from%20that.%26quot%3B%20It's%20kind%20of%20like%20buying%20a%20second%20pair%20of%20the%20same%20pants%20you%20like%20because%20they%20fit%20well%20and%20are%20durable%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20nice%20to%20have%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20deliver%20the%20same%20little%20burst%20of%20endorphins%20you%20got%20when%20you%20discovered%20the%20first%20pair.%20And%20the%20tax%20cut%20legislation%20is%20still%20months%20away.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20investors%20are%20being%20hit%20with%20daily%20headlines%20about%20all%20the%20less-business-friendly%20stuff%20Trump%20wants%20to%20do.%20It's%20like%20having%20to%20pay%20a%20bunch%20of%20medical%20bills%20while%20waiting%20for%20that%20pair%20of%20pants%20to%20get%20delivered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20sequencing%20is%20definitely%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20front-loading%20all%20of%20the%20tariffs%20and%20immigration%20risks%20this%20time%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20necessarily%20get%20the%20added%20juice%20from%20the%20fiscal%20side.%20I%20would%20argue%20you%20get%20none%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20belated%20Mnuchin%20mania%20is%20the%20manifestation%20of%20broader%20anxieties%20about%20the%20Trump%20administration%20and%20a%20recognition%20that%20this%20time%20really%20is%20different.%20Trump%20is%20moving%20faster%20and%20breaking%20things%20quicker.%20He%20feels%20like%20he%20has%20a%20mandate.%20He's%20bringing%20more%20true%20believers%20with%20him.%20Remember%20that%20supposed%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2017%2F12%2F15%2Fthe-committee-to-save-america-1513304754%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommittee%20to%20save%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20of%20people%20surrounding%20Trump%20to%20rein%20him%20in%20back%20in%202017%3F%20They%20are%20not%20invited%20to%20the%20party%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScott%20Bessent%20has%20Wall%20Street%20experience%2C%20but%20he%20doesn't%20seem%20particularly%20comfortable%20in%20how%20he%20talks%20about%20what%20it%20is%20that%20the%20administration's%20trying%20to%20achieve.%20What%20is%20the%20nonpartisan%20basis%20for%20it%3F%20What%20is%20the%20sort%20of%20substantive%20case%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Skanda%20Amarnath%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20Employ%20America%2C%20an%20economic%20advocacy%20group.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20who's%20currently%20picked%20is%20really%20indexing%20even%20further%20on%20loyalty%2C%20but%20that%20does%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20being%20credible%20in%20an%20economic%20markets%20context.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there's%20some%20rose-colored%20glasses%20stuff%20going%20on%20with%20the%20way%20many%20people%20think%20of%20Trump%201.0%2C%20at%20least%20money-wise.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20was%20up%20for%20most%20of%20his%20first%20term%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20a%20smooth%20ride%3B%20the%20index%20ended%202018%20down%20by%206.24%25.%20The%20US%20had%20a%20mild%20manufacturing%20recession%20in%202019.%20Many%20people%20in%20Trump's%20first%20administration%20were%20just%20as%20loyal%20to%20the%20president%20as%20those%20in%20the%20second%20administration.%20And%20ultimately%2C%20he%20was%20always%20the%20one%20in%20charge.%20It's%20not%20like%20Steven%20Mnuchin%20or%20Gary%20Cohn%20or%20Rex%20Tillerson%20were%20running%20around%20willy-nilly%20doing%20whatever%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20Dow%20was%20up%20for%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20everyone%20in%20human%20history%2C%20Mnuchin's%20record%20is%20mixed%20(and%20would%20get%20vastly%20different%20scores%2C%20depending%20on%20who%20you%20ask).%20He%20reportedly%20pushed%20for%20Trump%20to%20select%20Jerome%20Powell%20for%20Federal%20Reserve%20chair%2C%20whom%20many%20in%20finance%20and%20economics%20would%20agree%20was%20a%20sound%20choice.%20When%20the%20economy%20spiraled%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20he%20was%20a%20key%20negotiator%20in%20getting%20legislative%20support%20across%20the%20finish%20line.%20He%20also%20advocated%20for%20a%20tax%20bill%20that%20added%20to%20the%20deficit%20and%20disproportionately%20benefited%20corporations%20and%20the%20wealthy.%20And%20you%20have%20to%20admit%20that%20posing%20with%20the%20sheet%20of%20dollars%20was%20a%20little%20gauche%2C%20even%20if%20anyone%20in%20their%20right%20mind%20would%20have%20done%20the%20same%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20was%20pragmatic%2C%26quot%3B%20Amarnath%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20also%20had%20a%20certain%20credibility%20with%20the%20markets%20and%20political%20actors%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20aisle%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%2C%20all%20you%20Mnuchin%20heads%2C%20is%20he%20may%20be%20gone%2C%20but%20not%20forgotten.%20Back%20in%20November%2C%20he%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmnuchin-wont-rejoin-trump-administration-has-advice-sanctions-debt-2024-11-10%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2