%3E%3Cli%3ECol.%20Jeremy%20Cannon%20warned%20that%20trauma%20surgeons%20aren't%20getting%20enough%20cases%20to%20make%20them%20combat-ready.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20been%20growing%20concern%20that%20only%2010%25%20of%20US%20military%20doctors%20are%20ready%20for%20a%20peer%20conflict.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military's%20surgeons%20aren't%20getting%20nearly%20enough%20experience%20with%20trauma%20patients%20to%20be%20ready%20for%20a%20major%20war%2C%20a%20former%20Air%20Force%20surgeon%20warned%20Congress%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20actively%20falling%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20the%20peacetime%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20Ret.%20Col.%20Jeremy%20Cannon%20said%20at%20a%20Senate%20Armed%20Services%20Committee%20hearing%20on%20the%20state%20of%20medical%20care%20in%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECannon%2C%20who%20deployed%20to%20Iraq%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-afghanistan-tiktok-adventure-taliban-tourism-influencers-ak47s-selfie-sticks-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAfghanistan%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20trauma%20surgeon%2C%20warned%20in%20his%20accompanying%20statement%20to%20Congress%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bsystematic%20erosion%26quot%3B%20of%20medical%20readiness%20while%20US%20adversaries%20grow%20stronger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20the%20cost%20of%20this%20erosion%3F%20It%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-warned-golden-hour-save-soldiers-threatened-russia-ukraine-lost-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeasured%20in%20lives%20lost%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20one%20in%20four%20battlefield%20deaths%20are%20potentially%20survivable%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Cannon%2C%20who%20was%20director%20of%20the%20Defense%20Department's%20sole%20trauma%20center%20for%20the%20most%20severe%2C%20or%20Level%20One%2C%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20other%20participants%20at%20the%20hearing%20repeatedly%20referenced%20an%20analysis%20from%20Harvard%2C%20Rutgers%2C%20Deloitte%2C%20and%20military%20researchers%2C%20which%20found%20that%20only%2010%25%20of%20military%20surgeons%20were%20ready%20for%20war%20in%202019%20%E2%80%94%20down%20from%2017%25%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProjections%20estimate%20that%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-possible-war-2027-china-taiwan-invasion-lisa-franchetti-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeer%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20produce%20as%20many%20as%201%2C000%20casualties%20per%20day%20for%20100%20days%20straight%20or%20more%2C%20a%20scale%20not%20seen%20since%20World%20War%20II%2C%26quot%3B%20Cannon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNeither%20the%20current%20MHS%20nor%20the%20civilian%20sector%20can%20absorb%20this%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20Military%20Health%20System.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20testimony%2C%20he%20spoke%20of%20a%20US%20Army%20sergeant%20in%20Afghanistan%20who%20was%20hit%20in%20the%20chest%20by%20a%20sniper%20bullet%20in%202010%20but%20survived%20after%20receiving%20a%20lung%20and%20heart%20bypass%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECannon%20said%20that%20with%20today's%20standards%2C%20he%20feared%20the%20sergeant%20would%20have%20died%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20it%20took%20us%20three%20to%20four%20years%20to%20develop%20a%20trauma%20system%20in%20theater%20and%20another%20five%20to%20six%20years%20to%20achieve%20the%20medical%20supremacy%20that%20allowed%20us%20to%20save%20Sgt%20Ramirez%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20not%20have%2010%20years%20in%20the%20next%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2212d8402d-a865-43a8-9ded-534073fa58b1%5C%22%3EMilitary%20doctors%20are%20'scrounging'%20for%20cases%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECannon%20urged%20the%20US%20to%20designate%20five%20or%20six%20trauma%20facilities%20dedicated%20to%20severe%20cases%2C%20which%20would%20be%20staffed%20with%20military%20doctors.%20By%20funneling%20more%20civilian%20and%20troop%20cases%20to%20those%20centers%20%E2%80%94%20instead%20of%20spreading%20them%20across%20the%20national%20system%20%E2%80%94%20those%20surgeons%20will%20get%20regular%20exposure%20to%20treating%20such%20injuries%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20meanwhile%2C%20many%20military%20surgeons%20are%20%26quot%3Bscrounging%20around%26quot%3B%20for%20enough%20trauma%20cases%20to%20get%20experience%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20other%20witnesses%20at%20the%20hearing%20%E2%80%94%20Ret.%20Maj.%20Gen.%20Paul%20Friedrichs%20and%20Ret.%20Lt.%20Gen.%20Douglas%20Robb%20%E2%80%94%20expressed%20similar%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20descoped%20our%20facilities%20to%20the%20point%20where%20they%20take%20care%20of%20low-acuity%20community%20hospital%20patients%2C%20not%20trauma%20patients%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Friedrichs%2C%20who%20was%20command%20surgeon%20of%20the%20Joint%20Staff%20in%20the%20Pentagon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20witnesses%20called%20for%20the%20US%20government%20to%20see%20funding%20for%20casualty%20care%20as%20an%20investment%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-taiwan-war-us-no-allies-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efuture%20wars%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20not%20a%20burdensome%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20address%20the%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%2C%20and%20that's%20resourcing%2C%26quot%3B%20Friedrichs%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20medical%20inflation%20rate%2C%20on%20average%2C%20since%201938%2C%20is%205.1%25%20per%20year%2C%20and%20the%20military%20has%20seen%20a%20net%2012%25%20reduction%20in%20funding%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20way%20to%20fix%20these%20problems%20if%20the%20military%20health%20system%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20bill-payer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFriedrichs%20also%20warned%20of%20vulnerabilit