Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20our%20late%2020s%2C%20and%20we%20only%20contributed%20a%20nominal%20percentage%20of%20our%20incomes%20at%20the%20time.%20Now%20that%20I%20know%20and%20understand%20the%20magic%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20wish%20we%20had%20contributed%20much%20more%20than%20we%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20is%2C%20investing%20as%20regularly%20and%20early%20as%20possible%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20benefit%20from%20compound%20interest%20so%20you%20can%20retire%20when%20you%20want%2C%20and%20on%20your%20own%20terms.%20After%20all%2C%20investing%20early%20lets%20you%20begin%20building%20up%20a%20nest%20egg%20that%20increases%20in%20value%20over%20time%2C%20and%20compound%20interest%20eventually%20lets%20you%20grow%20wealth%20off%20of%20wealth%20you%20already%20earned%20on%20your%20investments%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20an%20example%2C%20consider%20this%20financial%20scenario%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20you%20invest%20%241%2C500%20a%20month%20for%2030%20years%20starting%20at%20age%2030%2C%20which%20means%20you%20are%20making%20%24540%2C000%20in%20contributions%20over%20that%20time.%20If%20you%20earned%20an%20average%20yield%20of%207%25%2C%20you%20would%20end%20the%2030-year%20period%20at%20age%2060%20with%20just%20over%20%241.7%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20imagine%20you%20invest%20%242%2C250%20for%2020%20years%20starting%20at%20age%2040%2C%20which%20means%20you%20are%20making%20the%20same%20%24540%2C000%20in%20investments%20over%20a%20shorter%20timeline.%20With%20the%20same%207%25%20yield%2C%20you%20would%20end%20the%2020%20years%20at%20age%2060%20with%20just%20over%20%241.106%20million%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227762bd4-57cf-4250-b53b-bfefc8a2e9d1%5C%22%3